<doc>
  <member name="DIRECTMANIPULATION_INPUT_MODE">
    <summary>
      <para>Defines the threading behavior for <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//previous-versions/windows/desktop/api/directmanipulation/nf-directmanipulation-idirectmanipulationviewport-setinputmode">SetInputMode</a> or <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//previous-versions/windows/desktop/api/directmanipulation/nf-directmanipulation-idirectmanipulationviewport-setupdatemode">SetUpdateMode</a>. The exact meaning of each constant depends on the method called.</para>
    </summary>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//previous-versions/windows/desktop/directmanipulation/direct-manipulation-enumerations">Direct Manipulation Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="DIRECTMANIPULATION_INPUT_MODE.DIRECTMANIPULATION_INPUT_MODE_AUTOMATIC">
    <summary>
      <para>Input is automatically passed to the viewport in an independent thread.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DIRECTMANIPULATION_INPUT_MODE.DIRECTMANIPULATION_INPUT_MODE_MANUAL">
    <summary>
      <para>Input is manually passed by   the app on its thread via the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//previous-versions/windows/desktop/api/directmanipulation/nf-directmanipulation-idirectmanipulationmanager-processinput">ProcessInput</a> method.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>